chat_history.content:
I'm sorry, I couldn't find a definitive list of the top 5 most viewed Disney Channel episodes. However, I did come across some information about the most viewed episodes of various Disney Channel shows.

**"Hannah Montana"**
The pilot episode of "Hannah Montana," titled "Lilly, Do You Want to Know a Secret?" is one of the series' most popular episodes, with 5.7 million viewers. The series ran for 4 seasons and a total of 98 episodes.

**"Phineas and Ferb"**
Season 4 episode 16, titled "Last Day of Summer," is the most-watched episode of the series, with 4.3 million viewers. The show ran for 4 seasons and a total of 133 episodes.

**"Wizards of Waverly Place"**
Season 2 episode 19, "Paint by Committee," is considered the show's most viewed episode, with 5.9 million viewers. The series had a total of 106 episodes across 4 seasons.

**"The Suite Life of Zack & Cody"**
"The Suite Life on Deck" is the most watched episode of the show, with 5.7 million viewers. It is part of a series that ran for 3 seasons, consisting of a total of 75 episodes.

**"Kim Possible"**
The second episode of season 4, "A Sitch in Time," is the most popular episode of the series, with 4.9 million viewers. "Kim Possible" had 84 episodes across its 4 seasons.

Please note that the information about the total number of episodes and their corresponding seasons may be subject to change as Disney Channel shows are constantly being added to and updated.
